                                                                                                                       7                                      Lorgat: ICC Test tourney in 2013
                      
	London: The International Cricket Council (ICC) has hinted that a Test Championship might be conducted in 2013 in England to revive fans interest in the longer version, which is struggling due to the growing popularity of Twenty20s.         
	ICC chief executive Haroon Lorgat said that the governing body is looking at ways to revive the dwindling interest in the five-day game.         
	Theres real talk of a Test play-off in the not too distant future... Theres a slot in 2013 that we think could work, he said. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
